---
description: Comprehensive error handling for every async and IO operation
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

Error handling is non-negotiable:

- Every async operation needs try/catch with a meaningful error message
- Every WebSocket event needs an error handler
- Camera permission denied: show user-friendly message explaining why camera is needed
- Mic permission denied: show message, continue without audio (camera still works)
- Network failures: show "Reconnecting..." state, not a blank screen or crash
- JSON parse errors on incoming WebSocket messages: log and skip, don't crash the session
- Never swallow exceptions silently. Log server-side, show user-friendly surface messages.
- Use a logger utility, not console.log in production code
